LUATION OF THE COLOMBIAN INSTITUTE OF CULTURE (COLCULTURA)'S EXPERIMENTALPROGRAMME OF PUBLIC-SCHOOL LIBRARIES.REPORT OF A STUDY CARRIED OUT BY THE COLUMBIAN INTERAMERICAN SCHOOL OFLIBRARIANSHIP, EVALUATING A 4-YEAR TRIAL IN 4 CITIES BEGUN IN 1972, TOESTABLISH WHETHER OR NOT TO CONTINUE AND EXPAND THE PROGRAMME. DETAILS AREGIVEN OF THE METHODOLOGY, AND A SUMMARY OF RESULTS PRESENTED, COVERING SUCHPOINTS AS USER ATTITUDES AND SATISFACTION; INTEGRATION WITH SCHOOL CURRICULA;AND ADEQUACY OF COLLECTIONS, PERSONNEL, AND SERVICES. FROM THESE, IT WASCONCLUDED THAT RELATIONS BETWEEN SCHOOLS AND LIBRARIES WERE DEFICIENT,RESULTING IN INADEQUATE LIBRARY INTEGRATION INTO EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMMES;TRAINING FOR THE LIBRARIANS INVOLVED IS STRONGLY RECOMMENDED AS A PRIMARYMEASURE TOWARDS IMPROVING THE PROJECT IF IT IS TO BE USED AS A MODEL FORFURTHER DEVELOPMENT